cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a data-driven approach for joint parameter and topology estimation in distribution grids, which involves modeling input and output measurement errors simultaneously using an error-in-variables (EIV) model in a maximum likelihood estimation (MLE) framework. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of systems and control (cs.SY), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with the integration of distributed energy resources (DERs) in distribution grids, which could also place it in the sub-categories of software engineering (cs.SE) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
